netcat usage Resource:
1. 1. server not killed when session is terminated using (-k) flag
2. kill session after a specified timeout period using the -w flag [mutually exclusive with the -l flag]
3. Don't kill client session when EOF is hit using the -q flag

4. Disabling Reading from STDIN in Netcat on the client side

# connect to server using the following
> nc -d localhost srv_port

# The text input at client side will not reach to server thread.

